## FILE 13: `src/app/pages/itemLibrary/gallery/gallery.component.ts`

Selector `app-item-gallery`. Regular Angular component.

Imports needed: `Component, Input, Output, EventEmitter` from `@angular/core`.

Inputs:
- `@Input() items: any[] = []`
- `@Input() selectedIds: Set<any> = new Set()`
- `@Input() density: 'comfortable' | 'compact' = 'comfortable'`

Outputs:
- `@Output() selectionChange = new EventEmitter<{item: any; checked: boolean}>()`
- `@Output() itemOpen = new EventEmitter<any>()`

Methods:
- `isSelected(item: any): boolean` → `this.selectedIds.has(item.id)`
- `onCheck(item: any, checked: boolean)` → emit `selectionChange`
- `onDblClick(item: any)` → emit `itemOpen`
- `getStatusTone(status: string)`: same status→tone lookup as status-pill (inline the map here — full copy)
- `getPropertyDot(item: any): string`: hash `String(item.property || item.property_id || '')` → `hsl(${hue} 45% 52%)`
- `getTileGradient(item: any): string`: hash same string → `linear-gradient(150deg, hsl(${h} 46% 95%), hsl(${h} 40% 87%))`
- `getTileBorder(item: any): string`: → `1px solid hsl(${h} 30% 80%)`
- `getThumbSrc(item: any): string | null`: → `item?.pic?.Thumbnail || item?.pic?.FullSizePicture || null`

